title: Live Chat: Leafs open season against Habs
text:
Leafs 'going to work extremely hard' TORONTO - 
We interrupt this Blue Jays fever - albeit only momentarily - to usher in the 2015-16 Maple Leafs regular season opener. 
Look at it this way, people - the Leafs are tied for first place in the entire National Hockey League. 
Of course, they haven't played a game yet. Details, details ... 
In any event, the curtain rises on the brand new campaign Wednesday night when the Leafs host Carey Price, P.K. Subban and the Montreal Canadiens at the Air Canada Centre. 
With Blue Jays catcher Russell Martin scheduled to be in the house, coach Mike Babcock will make his regular season debut behind the Leafs bench. How will he fare? 
For all things, Leafs-Habs, join Sun hockey columnist Mike Zeisberger for our live chat starting at 6:45 p.m. EST. Questions, comments and rants are welcome.
